  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-10-01",
    "date": "2003-10-31T19:40:13Z",
    "text": "Business Activity Tax Simplification Act of 2003 - Amends Federal law concerning the taxation of interstate commerce to expand the scope of the protections prohibiting taxation by jurisdictions of the income of out-of-state corporations whose in-state presence is nominal from just tangible personal property to include intangible property and services.\n\nRequires an out-of-state company to have a physical presence in a State before the State can impose franchise taxes, business license taxes, and other business activity taxes."
  },
